text:
Stopping power runs counter to follow up power, so skill and familiarity are more important. If you give your mama a .45 acp and the first time she fires it is in self defense she is very likely to A) miss because pulling the trigger without pulling your aim sideways with a pistol is harder than people think it is, B) lose her grip or hurt her wrist from recoil, C) smack herself in the forehead like I did.
The argument for .22 comes from the lack of recoil, mama can mag dump all 15 rounds in about 5 seconds and have a high chance of most of them hitting the attacker, and the risk of over penetration is very low.
